                  <provenance type="MLGB3_provenance_evidence" source="http://mlgb3.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/mlgb/book/6027">Written at an unknown centre. Probably at Worcester by the third quarter of the 12th century.
                     <orgName role="fmo" key="org_148943477">Worcester, Worcestershire, Benedictine cathedral priory of St Mary the Virgin</orgName> (?) : Papal letter to Roger, bp. of Worcester (s. xii) added on the originally blank recto of the first leaf (fol. 1r).     Fol. 1v has the note ":9 et est liber dialogorum Gregorii [pape] 2 o  fo. in monasterio etc."; "prec xiii s viii d" (s. xiv). (<ref target="http://mlgb3.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/mlgb/book/6027">MLGB3</ref>: evidence from locally specific contents, including obits, scribbles, etc.). </provenance>
